ing pesd where he is collaborating with mark thurber and xander slaski on multiple research projects related to diffusion of sustainable cookstoves in india gireesh holds a phd from stanford university a ms from university of minnesota and a btech from indian institute of technology new delhi he also has close to nine years experience in the high tech industry publications cover improved stoves in india a study of sustainable business models gireesh shrimali xander slaski mark c thurber hisham zerriffi energy policy 2011 html+ pdf+ events & presentations energy working group talk the role of the private sector in the diffusion of improved cookstoves may 19 2010 research seminar gireesh shrimali search people everything news around the web going green er planning the next era of environmental regulation in india many large indian conglomerates are undertaking efforts to become more environmentally friendly according to gireesh shrimali professor of information october 21 2010 in knowledge wharton support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 724 1714 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
